                    EARTH SCIENCE > OCEANS > BATHYMETRY/SEAFLOOR TOPOGRAPHY > SEAFLOOR TOPOGRAPHY

                    

                
                Definition:

                
                    General elevation pattern of the land surface or the ocean bottom.  Also refer
to as bathymetry, the study and mapping of sea floor elevations and the
variations of water depth; the topography of the sea floor.
                
                

                

                
                    Reference:

                    
                        
                            Alyn C. Duxbury, Alison B. Duxbury, and Keith A. Sverdrup. An Introduction to 
 the World's Oceans. 6th edition. McGraw-Hill Higher Education, 2000. 
                        
                    
                    

                    

                
            


       







    
    
    
        
    

    
